Standard and Poor's Corp said itaffirmed the ratings on 255 mln dlrs of debt of TriangleIndustries Inc and the unit National Can Corp.    S and P cited an increase in Triangle's equity base toabout 450 mln dlrs at year-end 1986 from 102 mln dlrs a yearago. That resulted from a conversion of debt securities and theissuance of equity to American Can Co &lt;AC> as part of thepurchase prices for American Can's packaging operations.    Affirmed were Triangle's B-minus subordinated debt andpreferred stock and National Can's B-plus senior debt andB-minus subordinated debt. Reuter&#3;